From: elizaOS chip team <chip-team@elizaos.invalid>
Subject: [PATCH] cva6: btb.sv work around V3Delayed whole-array NBA limitation

The simulator 5.049 (devel rev v5.048-46-g7c5069c7d) aborts with

    Internal Error: ../V3Delayed.cpp:958: Unexpected LHS form

while lowering core/frontend/btb.sv:188 -- the whole-array non-blocking
assignment `btb_q <= btb_d;` to a 2D unpacked struct array

    btb_prediction_t btb_q[NR_ROWS-1:0][CVA6Cfg.INSTR_PER_FETCH-1:0]

The V3Delayed pass currently does not support whole-array NBA on 2D
unpacked struct arrays.  --lint-only succeeds because the failure is in
the elaboration-to-C++ lowering, not in lint.

This patch replaces the whole-array NBA with an explicit per-element
nested for-loop.  The two forms are semantically equivalent (every
[i][j] element is non-blockingly assigned to the corresponding [i][j]
of btb_d on the same clock edge) but the per-element form exercises the
supported per-element NBA lowering path.

The replacement comment block intentionally avoids the literal token
"verilator" at the start of any C-style block: tools beginning a block
comment with that token treat the entire comment as a control-pragma
candidate and emit BADVLTPRAGMA.

Tracked in external/cva6/pin-manifest.json::verilator_full_conversion_blocker.
The patch is carried locally under patches/cva6/ and applied by
scripts/apply_cva6_patches.sh before each simulator run against the
CVA6 source tree.  Drop the patch when a release lands that lowers the
whole-array NBA form natively.
---
 core/frontend/btb.sv | 13 ++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/core/frontend/btb.sv b/core/frontend/btb.sv
index 139f655..96c70b8 100644
--- a/core/frontend/btb.sv
+++ b/core/frontend/btb.sv
@@ -185,7 +185,18 @@ module btb #(
             end
           end
         end else begin
-          btb_q <= btb_d;
+          // Local workaround for an internal-error in the C++ lowering
+          // pass on whole-array NBA to a 2D unpacked struct array
+          // (see V3Delayed.cpp:958 Unexpected LHS form).  The
+          // per-element nested loop below is semantically equivalent
+          // and exercises the supported per-element NBA path.  See
+          // patches/cva6/btb-v3delayed-workaround.patch in the
+          // consuming repo.
+          for (int i = 0; i < NR_ROWS; i++) begin
+            for (int j = 0; j < CVA6Cfg.INSTR_PER_FETCH; j++) begin
+              btb_q[i][j] <= btb_d[i][j];
+            end
+          end
         end
       end
     end
--
2.43.0
